
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `fc-list` baraye liste kardan font-haye mojood dar system shoma be kar miravad. Shoma mitavanid az an baraye peyda kardan name font-ha va style-haye mokhtalef estefade konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `fc-list`        --> 📜 Namayesh hameye font-ha ba etela'ate kamel.
    🔹 `fc-list :lang=fa` --> 🇮🇷 Namayesh font-hayi ke az zabane Farsi poshtibani mikonand.
    🔹 `fc-list family`  --> 👪 Namayesh listi az name-haye family-e font-ha.
    🔹 `fc-list object-path`  --> 📁 Namayesh masir (path) file-haye font.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ fc-list
    
    🔹 Liste kardan hameye font-ha va etela'ate aanha.

    $ fc-list :lang=en family style
    
    🔹 Namayesh family va style-haye font-hayi ke az zabane Englisi poshtibani mikonand.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ fc-list | grep "Arial"

    🔹 Peyda kardan font-haye Arial dar list font-ha. In dastoor az `grep` estefade mikonad ta natije-ha ra filtar konad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `fc-list` command is used to list the fonts available on your system.  You can use it to find font names and different styles.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `fc-list`            --> 📜 Display all fonts with complete information.
    🔹 `fc-list :lang=en`   --> 🇺🇸 Display fonts that support the English language.
    🔹 `fc-list family`     --> 👪 Display a list of font family names.
    🔹 `fc-list object-path` --> 📁 Display the file paths of the fonts.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ fc-list
    
    🔹 List all fonts and their information.

    $ fc-list :lang=en family style
    
    🔹 Show the family and styles of fonts that support the English language.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ fc-list | grep "Arial"

    🔹 Find Arial fonts in the font list. This command uses `grep` to filter the results.
